Hi <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     My last post was to help others to try and understand the history of the Magician class, so as to not judge us as some mana battery with no offensive capabilities<br>
<br>
This post has a lot more numbers to it and will try to cover the nuking comparisons between Wizards, Mages, Druids, Enchanters, and Clerics as they were before Kunark, during kunark, during velious, luclin and the PoP spells as they are now.  Some remain skeptical about our nuking powers diminishing while others just want some numbers, I'm gonna provide those the best I can <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Granted this isn't going to be all-inclusive and most likely I'll miss a few things but it's my best shot at determining damage output and honestly Im writing this before I even see the numbers so they'll be new to me as well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
Now, a few things to take into consideration when viewing these numbers is that I tested DPS with no focus items or AA and then again with those two added.  Also, I further divided the tests into 5 minute fights, and then a 20 minute fight to try and simulate some Velious and all Luclin encounters.   Old world and Kunark are not included in the 20 minute fights as there were none.  The Planes of Power numbers are not going to be completely accurate as I had to make some educated guesses on mana pool.  The following is the adjustments and constants in the tests<br>
<br>
Old World Era<br>
Constants: The mana pool of players were limited to a max of 2000, to include gear and Int.  Then I added in mana gained through Bard songs and Clarity and added that total to the max mana of the player. No one had flowing thought as it was not in the game.  <br>
Adjustments: Wizards gained 250 additional mana from Harvest but lost 10 seconds due to the stun.  <br>
Total base mana in 5 minute test: 2650<br>
<br>
Kunark Era<br>
Constants: The mana of players were raised to 3000 to simulate the increase of 10 levels and slightly better caster gear.  The upgraded spells of Clarity 2 and Bard songs were added as well<br>
Adjustments: Wizards gained 326 additional mana from Harvest, but were stunned for 10 seconds<br>
Total base mana in 5 minute test:  4200<br>
<br>
Velious Era<br>
Constants: Mana pool of players is raised to 3700 to account for the much improved gear in Velious.  Gift of Brillance and Protection of the Glades were added to mana regen of all players ontop of Clarity 2 and Bard songs.  All characters were also given flowing thought 2.  <br>
Adjustments: Wizards gained 326 additional mana from Harvest and an extra 3mana/tick from their Epic.  <br>
Total base mana in 5 minute test: 5450<br>
Total base mana in 20 minute test: 10,650<br>
<br>
Luclin Era<br>
Constants: Mana pool is raised to 4200 for all players.  Kodiac’s Endless Intellect, Protection of the Glades and Bard song are considered to be on every player.  All players are also considered to have Flowing Thought 8 and be carry a single Rod of Mystical Transvergence.  For the modified tests all players have Spell Casting Mastery 3 and Spell Casting Fury 3.  <br>
Adjustments: Wizards gain 326 mana from harvest and 150 mana from Greater Familiar.  Also they have an additional 7mana/tick regen from Greater Familiar and their epic.  They are also given Spell Casting Fury Mastery 3.  Enchanters are given the Gather Mind ability but they only gain half the normal mana assuming you fight a mob every hour and the skill has a reuse time of over 2, Magicians are considered to have Elemental Form: Water 3, Druids have Quick Damage 3 as well.  <br>
Total base mana in 5 minute test: 7426<br>
Total base mana in 20 minute test: 13,310<br>
<br>
Planes of Power Era (Estimated)<br>
Constants: Mana pool is raised to 4600.  All players have the improved mana regen spells from both Bards, Enchanters and Druids.  Flowing Thought is raised to 13 and each player has a Rod of Mystical Transvergence.  Players have the same skills as before and same adjustments.<br>
Adjustments.  As before, but wizards now gained 450 mana from the new harvest spell.  <br>
Total base mana in 5 minute test: 8160<br>
Total base mana in 20 minute test: 17,360<br>
