To figure out the number of nukes that a class could do I just divided their total mana by the spell cost.  Then I took the amount of time it took to cast that number of nukes and subtracted it from the total time in seconds (300 for 5 mins, 1200 for 20 mins).  After I figured out the remaining seconds I divided that by 6 to see the amount of ticks, then multiplied the number of ticks by the amount of mana you gain through meditation (20 in pre kunark, 24 after that).  The mana gained from medding was then divided by the nuke cost again to see how many extra nukes the class could of done with the extra mana.  To get the DPS (damage per second) for the class I just multiplied the total number of nukes by the damage of the nuke and then divided it by the total time in seconds.  What I did would look something like this.  Sorry Im not a math major J complete opposite<br>
<br>
Total Mana/Nuke Cost = # of nukes<br>
# of nukes * (castingtime+2.5) = # of seconds it takes to cast # of nukes<br>
Test Time - # of seconds = Amount of seconds left over<br>
Amount of seconds left over / 6 = # of ticks<br>
# of ticks * Meditation Rate = Bonus Mana gained during fight<br>
Bonus mana gained / Nuke cost = # of bonus nukes<br>
# of bonus nukes + # of nukes = Total # of nukes for the class<br>
Total # of nukes * Nuke damage / Test time = DPS<br>
<br>
If the total casting time exceeded the Test Time then I just subtracted an equal amount of nukes so that it would go below the Test Time.  AA and Focus effects tests were basically identical except the numbers were modified and I added in crits after I figured out the Total # of nukes (14% for wizards, 7% for everyone else).  Also the mana cost for Chanters and Clerics were based on 50 Evoc Specialization as I have never met one with 200.<br>
