Umm, I am not sure which hypothetical heal and situation you are using.  But druids can not heal as efficiently as a shaman/cleric(more so clerics, who are the core of the mod users).  A semi-competent cleric does not cast some heal on a 900 dmg mod hit.  Rather, they mod down to 40% or so and use complete heal.  High-end raid clerics are above 4k hps easy.  so 60% of 4000 hit points healed for 400 mana(and alot less including specs etc).  2400 hps/400 mana will beat out any druid heal.  <br>
<br>
In terms of efficiency, and leaving sentimentality aside, it is not a good idea for a druid to eat mods to nuke.  Wizards have far superior nukes, and would gain the full 660 mana on their dmg absorbing epics.  Druids will not be so fortunate, and will not even have better ratios on their nukes.  There just isn't a reason to do this.<br>
<br>
If PoP comes out, and druids get a CH spell, then I definately could see them getting as many rods as they want to help with healing, but that is not the current case.<br>
